      "description": "EmployeeLevelWorkflow represents the lifecycle state of an employee level.\nState machine: DRAFT → SUBMITTED → APPROVED → RELEASED.\nBypass: users with bypass permission can jump from any pre-release state to RELEASED.\n\n - EMPLOYEE_LEVEL_WORKFLOW_UNSPECIFIED: Default / unset.\n - EMPLOYEE_LEVEL_WORKFLOW_DRAFT: Draft — not yet published.\n - EMPLOYEE_LEVEL_WORKFLOW_RELEASED: Released — active and in use.\n - EMPLOYEE_LEVEL_WORKFLOW_SUPER_USER: Super user — reserved for top-level system access.\n - EMPLOYEE_LEVEL_WORKFLOW_SUBMITTED: Submitted — pending approval.\n - EMPLOYEE_LEVEL_WORKFLOW_APPROVED: Approved — approved, pending release."
